HEADWORD: out-tray
<hw>out-tray</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a wood or metal receptacle placed
on a desk to hold documents which have been processed, prior to transfer
to a different person.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> out-basket.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

